<LP>
   WASTE MANAGEMENT Inc. (Oak Brook, Ill.) -- D.P. Payne,
currently a vice president and Midwest area general manager
for International Business Machines Corp., was named a senior
vice president at this waste-handling concern, effective Aug.
1. Mr. Payne, 47 years old, will become one of three senior
vice presidents at the company; in the newly created post, he
will be responsible for Waste Management's strategic
planning, sales and marketing, information systems and
quality control. Separately, Waste Management named Thomas C.
Hau, 54, currently a partner at the accounting firm of Arthur
Andersen &amp; Co., as vice president, controller, effective
Sept. 1. In that post, he succeeds Jerry Girsch, who remains
a vice president and now will serve as controller for Waste
Management's North American operation, in addition to his
other operating duties.
</LP>
