EARNINGS (ERN)
MEDICAL SUPPLIES (MDS)
</IN>
<LP>
   Abbott Laboratories, North Chicago, Ill., citing
"continued productivity improvement, higher volume and better
product mix," said second-quarter earnings climbed 13%, on a
14% increase in sales.
   The maker of hospital products and pharmaceuticals
reported second-quarter earnings of $240.2 million, or 55
cents a share, up from $212.6 million, or 48 cents, a year
earlier. Per-share figures reflect a decrease in shares
outstanding to 437.1 million from 447.8 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales were $1.50 billion in the latest quarter, up from
$1.32 billion.
   Abbott chairman and chief executive officer Duane L.
Burnham said the company expects to report record sales and
earnings "for the 19th consecutive year" in 1990.
   For the six months, Abbott's net income was $465.2
million, or $1.06 a share, up 15% from last year's $410.5
million, or 92 cents a share. Sales in the period rose 13% to
$2.94 billion from $2.61 billion.
